<ingredient>3 TBsp olive oil</ingredient>
<ingredient>1 can black beans</ingredient>
<ingredient>1 egg</ingredient>
<ingredient>1/4 cup bread crumbs </ingredient>
<ingredient>2 green onions chopped </ingredient>
<ingredient>1 teaspoon cumin and coriander</ingredient>
<ingredient>1 teaspoon mustard </ingredient>
<ingredient>2 garlic cloves crushed</ingredient>
<ingredient>1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper</ingredient>
<step>
Rinse and drain black beans, either pur√©e in blender or mash with a fork in a bowl.  Add the other ingredients, except the oil and mix well with your hands. Form into four even patties. Heat the oil in a pan and cook on each side for 4 minutes each side. Serve with salad or inside a burger bun.
